txt.en: You have discovered the nest of Blackbeak! You should defeat this vile craban.
Crebain gather upon Cracabor and fly to the surrounding lands, spying upon all that roams below.

'Do you see the crebain watching us from above? They are from Cracabor -- I have seen them gather upon the crest of that high hill. My heart warns that these are no ordinary birds. The crebain seem guided by some unseen hand; they move about as if with purpose.\n\n'See how they stare! I cannot help but feel that I am being spied upon. I would appreciate if you could climb Cracabor and find out what you can about those vile birds.'
The hill of Cracabor is the highest point in the Wold, located just south of Wódscrafen, and north of Twickenburg.\n\nYou should climb Cracabor and scout its height.

'You found an evil object upon the crest of Cracabor? Perhaps it is the work of that Nazgûl you spied earlier; he may have summoned the crebain. The black birds are surely spies for some evil plot....'
Sergeant Tidlac is keeping watch on the road from the fort of Twickenburg, between Harwick and Floodwend.\n\nYou should speak with Sergeant Tidlac of what you found.
